ANTHRAX - PAKISTAN (04): (FEDERALLY ADMINISTERED TRIBAL AREAS) BOVINE
*********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 11 Nov 2017
Source: Dawn [edited]
https://www.dawn.com/news/1369729/anthrax-kills-several-animals-in-bajaur


A mysterious disease, declared by livestock officials as anthrax, has reportedly killed a number of animals in Bajaur Agency [Federally Administered Tribal Areas, FATA] over the last few days, locals told Dawn on Friday [10 Nov 2017].

They said several cattle had died of the disease during the past 2 weeks in various localities of Mamond and Khar tehsils. According to them, a number of cattle had also been infected with the disease.

The locals said the disease had panicked them, as they could not afford the loss of their precious animals.

The people said that following the deaths of the animals, officials of the local livestock department had visited the affected areas and obtained information about the disease. According to them, livestock officials examined the infected cattle and vaccinated a number of animals in the localities.

Meanwhile, livestock department officials said the disease might be anthrax. However, assistant director of livestock and dairy development, Dr Ahmad Younis, declared the disease as anthrax. But, he rejected the local people's claim that a number of cattle had been killed by the disease. He clarified that anthrax disease was reported in Chengazo area of Khar, where, so far, only one cow had been killed.

He said that soon after receiving information about the outbreak of the disease that teams had been dispatched to the affected area to administer anti-anthrax vaccines to cattle.

